      "content": "Of course! Let's make your trip to Tokyo as smooth as a well-oiled goblin machine. First, you'll want to use the Tokyo Metro Ginza Line to get from Shibuya to Marunouchi. It's a direct line, so you'll be there in no time. Aim to catch the Shibuya Station exit and hop on the Ginza Line, which will take you straight to Marunouchi Station.\n\nAs for those quiet cafes, I recommend trying \"Kissa Yokocho\" in Akihabara. It's a hidden gem where you can work in peace, surrounded by the hum of other workaday goblins. Another great spot is \"Nakamise Street\" near Senso-ji Temple. It's a bustling market, but if you find a corner away from the crowds, you'll have a peaceful spot to get some work done. And don't forget to try \"Café de la Paix\" in Ginza; it's a classic spot for a quiet coffee break.\n\nRemember, goblins are always on the move, so make sure to keep your travel times in mind and plan accordingly. Safe travels, my friend!",
